  • Constructor Details

    • ExpandingLimitedPrecisionIndexingTree

      public ExpandingLimitedPrecisionIndexingTree​(Box domain, double precision)
      Constructor using an initial box to start with. This box can be later enlarged to fit items located outside the initial box.

      The precision argument is used to scale the coordinates internally: all coordinate values are multiplied by 1/precision and truncated to longs, so that exact comparison of locations becomes possible. Therefore, in this system, two or more items can have exactly the same location.

      Parameters:
      domain - the initial domain to start the tree with
      precision - the precision of coordinates - a distance smaller than precision is considered equal to zero
